## Why This Is Asked
Tests knowledge of in-place bitboard style transforms, pure bitwise logic, and branchless design for a fixed-width data layout.

## Key Concepts
- Bit-slice permutation across 8x8 matrix
- Masked swaps and shifts to perform transposition in O(1)
- Endianness and layout nullified by a consistent row-major interpretation

## Code Example
```javascript
function transpose8x8(x) {
  // Use BigInt for 64-bit arithmetic in JS
  let t;
  const m1 = 0x5555555555555555n;
  t = (x ^ (x >> 1n)) & m1;
  x = x ^ t ^ (t << 1n);

  const m2 = 0x3333333333333333n;
  t = (x ^ (x >> 2n)) & m2;
  x = x ^ t ^ (t << 2n);

  const m4 = 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0Fn;
  t = (x ^ (x >> 4n)) & m4;
  x = x ^ t ^ (t << 4n);

  return x;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
