- How would you handle different input mappings (column-major) or endianness concerns?

## Why This Is Asked

Parity computation over 128 bits tests the ability to design constant-time reductions using only bitwise operations and shifts, without loops or branches.

## Key Concepts
- Bitwise XOR folding across 128 bits
- Progressive reduction by shifting (64,32,16,8,4,2,1)
- Final extraction with a single bit AND

## Code Example
